.TH "ubifs_update_one_lp" 9 "ubifs_update_one_lp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubifs_update_one_lp \- update LEB properties.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubifs_update_one_lp
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "int lnum "  ","
.BI "int free "  ","
.BI "int dirty "  ","
.BI "int flags_set "  ","
.BI "int flags_clean "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
the UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "lnum" 12
LEB to change properties for
.IP "free" 12
amount of free space
.IP "dirty" 12
amount of dirty space to add
.IP "flags_set" 12
flags to set
.IP "flags_clean" 12
flags to clean
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is the same as '\fBubifs_change_one_lp\fP' but \fIdirty\fP is added to
current dirty space, not substitutes it.
